article.headline: Arkansas State 98, West Alabama 57
article.story: JONESBORO, Ark. (AP) -- J.J. Montgomery scored 24 points and Dewarick Spencer scored 23 in Arkansas State's 98-57 victory over West Alabama Monday night. Arkansas State (2-0) led throughout and held a 44-25 lead at halftime. For the game, the Indians shot 55 percent from the field and made 17 of 21 free throws. West Alabama shot 39 percent and was 8-of-13 from the free throw line. Spencer had eight assists for the Indians, which had won on the road at Ole Miss on Saturday. Joseph Baker had 13 points and 13 rebounds for West Alabama (0-5), and Nic Gragg scored 12 points.
